        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 2:53PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking several thunderstorms
across southern Madison and Gallatin counties, including a strong
thunderstorm 24 miles southeast of Virginia City, moving northeast
at 40 mph. This storm will be near the Big Sky area by around 330
PM.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone, Big Sky, Targhee Pass, and Yellowstone Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
